enigma_edit.lua.data

Interface TilePart

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Source, Typed
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TilePart.Construct, TilePart.Ref

    public interface TilePart
extends Source
    Part of a tile declaration. There are two types of objects that can make up a tile.
  • A simple tile declaration by a defining lua table (see TilePart.Construct).
  • A reference to an existing tile (see TilePart.Ref).

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  TilePart.Construct
      Any part of a tile declaration (that is not a reference to another tile).
      static class  TilePart.Ref
      This is a special FieldReference, that stores a reference to a member of the Tiles-Resolver.
